### 6. AI System vs. Traditional Firewall

| Feature | Traditional Firewall | AI-Powered System (Your Project) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Detection Method** | **Rule-Based:** Blocks traffic based on pre-set rules (e.g., "Block IP 1.2.3.4"). | **Behavior-Based:** Analyzes patterns and behaviors (e.g., "This traffic looks like a DDoS attack"). |
| **Unknown Threats** | **Fails:** Cannot detect new attacks (Zero-day) without a specific rule. | **Succeeds:** Can detect anomalies and unknown attacks based on deviation from normal behavior. |
| **Adaptability** | **Static:** Needs manual updates for every new threat. | **Dynamic:** Can be retrained to learn new threats automatically. |
| **Complexity** | Simple, fast, but limited. | Complex, intelligent, provides deep insights. |

